structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Projected population, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Australians, Australia, state and territories, 2021 to 2031
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Contains estimates and projections of the Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander population based on the 2016 Census of Population and Housing, by sex and five-year age groups, for the period 2006 to 2031. Population projections illustrate how the Australian Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander population would change in the future as a result of certain assumptions. This dataset presents 9 scenarios, comprising combinations of different rates of fertility, paternity, mortality, interstate migration and overseas migration. Unit of measure: Projected Persons. Geographic coverage: Australia/State. Catalogue number: 3238.0

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Projected population, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Australians, Remoteness Areas, 2021 to 2031
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Contains estimates and projections (based on assumptions on past and future fertility, mortality and migration) of the Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander population based on the 2016 Census of Population and Housing for Indigenous Regions and Remoteness Areas by sex and five-year age groups, for the period 2017 to 2031. Population projections illustrate how the Australian Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander population would change in the future as a result of certain assumptions. This dataset presents 9 scenarios, comprising combinations of different rates of fertility, paternity, mortality, interstate migration and overseas migration. Unit of measure: Projected Persons. Geographic coverage: Remoteness Areas. Catalogue number: 3238.0

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Projected population, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Australians, Indigenous Regions, 2021 to 2031
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Contains estimates and projections (based on assumptions on past and future fertility, mortality and migration) of the Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander population based on the 2016 Census of Population and Housing for Indigenous Regions and Remoteness Areas by sex and five-year age groups, for the period 2021 to 2031. Population projections illustrate how the Australian Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander population would change in the future as a result of certain assumptions. This dataset presents 9 scenarios, comprising combinations of different rates of fertility, paternity, mortality, interstate migration and overseas migration. Unit of measure: Projected Persons. Geographic coverage: Indigenous Regions. Catalogue number: 3238.0

Unit of measure: AUD millions, Index numbers. Geographic coverage: Australia. Catalogue number: 5302.0

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Balance of Payments by State
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Balance of Payments by State draws the state and territory series of balances between inward and outward transactions, provides an overall net flow of transactions between Australian states and territories and the rest of the world and reports how that flow is funded. Unit of measure: AUD Index. Geographic coverage: Australia. Catalogue number: 5302.0

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Building Activity
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Building Activity. Provides estimates of value of building work and number of dwellings commenced, completed, under construction and in the pipeline. Unit of measure: AUD Units. Geographic coverage: Australia/State. Catalogue number: 8752.0

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Monthly Business Turnover Indicator
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Experimental indicator of business turnover derived from monthly Business Activity Statements

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Building Work Done, Preliminary
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Provides preliminary estimates of value of total construction work done, building work done and engineering construction work done. Unit of measure: AUD. Geographic coverage: Australia/State. Catalogue number: 8755.0

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Census 2021, G01 Selected person characteristics by sex, Commonwealth Electoral Divisions (CED 2021 boundaries)
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Selected person characteristics by sex data for Commonwealth Electoral Divisions (CED 2021 boundaries), 2021 Census, Count of persons. This table is based on place of usual residence, except for counts by dwelling type which are based on place of enumeration and exclude overseas visitors. Eduction institution comprises 'Preschool', 'Primary' (including Government, Catholic, Other non-Government, Primary not further defined), 'Secondary' (including Government, Catholic, Other non-Government, Secondary not further defined) and 'Tertiary' (including vocational education (including TAFE and private training providers), university or other higher education, Tertiary not further defined). Excludes persons who did not state which type of education institution they were attending. Highest year of school completed is applicable to persons aged 15 years and over. Please note that there are small random adjustments made to all cell values to protect the confidentiality of data. These adjustments may cause the sum of rows or columns to differ by small amounts from table totals.

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Census 2021, G02 Selected medians and averages, Commonwealth Electoral Divisions (CED 2021 boundaries)
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Selected medians and averages data for Commonwealth Electoral Divisions (CED 2021 boundaries), 2021 Census. Median age of persons excludes overseas visitors. Median total personal income is applicable to persons aged 15 years and over. Median total family income is applicable to families in family households. It excludes families where at least one member aged 15 years and over did not state an income and families where at least one member aged 15 years and over was temporarily absent on Census Night. Median total household income is applicable to occupied private dwellings. It excludes households where at least one member aged 15 years and over did not state an income and households where at least one member aged 15 years and over was temporarily absent on Census Night. It excludes 'Visitors only' and 'Other non-classifiable' households. Median mortgage repayment is applicable to occupied private dwellings being purchased and includes dwellings being purchased under a shared equity scheme. It excludes 'Visitors only' and 'Other non-classifiable' households. Median rent is applicable to occupied private dwellings being rented. It excludes 'Visitors only' and 'Other non-classifiable' households. For 2021, median rent calculations exclude dwellings being 'Occupied rent-free' and will not be comparable to 2016 Census data. Average number of persons per bedroom is applicable to occupied private dwellings. It excludes 'Visitors only' and 'Other non-classifiable' households. Average household size is applicable to number of persons usually resident in occupied private dwellings. It includes partners, children, and co-tenants (in group households) who were temporarily absent on Census Night. A maximum of three temporary absentees can be counted in each household. It excludes 'Visitors only' and 'Other non-classifiable' households.

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Census 2021, G03 Place of usual residence by place of enumeration on Census Night by age, Commonwealth Electoral Divisions (CED 2021 boundaries)
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Place of usual residence by place of enumeration on Census Night by age data for Commonwealth Electoral Divisions (CED 2021 boundaries), 2021 Census, Count of persons (excludes overseas visitors). This table is based on place of enumeration. This table counts persons where they were staying on Census Night. It shows the number of persons who were at home on Census Night and the number of persons who were visiting away from their usual residence. For persons visiting away from their usual residence, it shows which SA2 they were visiting from, i.e. either interstate, intrastate or from within the same SA2 area. Please note that there are small random adjustments made to all cell values to protect the confidentiality of data. These adjustments may cause the sum of rows or columns to differ by small amounts from table totals.

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Census 2021, G21 Type of long-term health condition by selected person characteristics, Commonwealth Electoral Divisions (CED 2021 boundaries)
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Type of long-term health condition by selected person characteristics data for Commonwealth Electoral Divisions (CED 2021 boundaries), 2021 Census, Count of responses and persons. This table is based on place of usual residence. Measures the number of people who reported that they have been told by a doctor or nurse that they have any of these long-term health conditions. Includes health conditions that have lasted or are expected to last six months or more, may occur from time to time, are controlled by medication or are in remission. Respondents had the option to record multiple long-term health conditions therefore the sum of total responses count will not equal the total person count. Total personal income and Australia Defence Force service is applicable to persons aged 15 years and over. Core activity need for assistance is a person's need for help or assistance in one or more of the three core activity areas of self-care, mobility and communication, because of a disability, long-term health condition (lasting six months or more) or old age. Australian Defence Force service includes Royal Australian Navy, Australian Army, Royal Australian Air Force, Second Australian Imperial Force, National Service and NORFORCE. Excludes service for non-Australian Defence forces. Includes service in the Regular Service and/or Reserves Service. Please note that there are small random adjustments made to all cell values to protect the confidentiality of data. These adjustments may cause the sum of rows or columns to differ by small amounts from table totals.

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: Provisional Mortality Statistics: Number of deaths by Sex, Age and State of registration, by month of occurrence
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Provisional Monthly Mortality Statistics: Contains preliminary death counts by month of occurrence for Australia. Death counts include both doctor certified and coroner certified deaths. This series was introduced in June 2020 in response to the COVID-19 pandemic in Australia. This data provides an early indication of the pattern of mortality. There are many factors that influences counts of deaths on a monthly basis, including time required for coronial investigations and timeliness of death registrations. These considerations should be taken into account when interpreting data. Monthly occurrence data is available from 2015 onwards. Death counts are not comparable to those reported in Deaths, Australia or Causes of Death, Australia.

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: SEIFA 2011 by Postal Area Code (POA)
structure:Dataflow.common:Description: Consists of four indexes based on Census data: Index of Relative Socio-economic Disadvantage (IRSD); Index of Relative Socio-economic Advantage and Disadvantage (IRSAD); Index of Education and Occupation (IEO) and Index of Economic Resources (IER). Each index is a summary of Census variables and focuses on a different aspect of socio-economic advantage and disadvantage. Postal Areas are an ABS approximation of postcodes (post codes) created to enable the release of ABS data on areas that, as closely as possible, approximate postcodes. This enables the comparison of ABS data with other data collected using postcodes as the geographic reference. Unit of measure: Index. Geographic coverage: ASGS2011 Postal Code Area (POA). Catalogue number: 2033.0.55.001

structure:Dataflow.common:Name: SEIFA 2011 by State Suburb Code (SSC)

It consists of four indexes based on Census data: Index of Relative Socio-economic Disadvantage (IRSD); Index of Relative Socio-economic Advantage and Disadvantage (IRSAD); Index of Education and Occupation (IEO) and Index of Economic Resources (IER). Each index is a summary of a different subset of Census variables and focuses on a different aspect of socio-economic advantage and disadvantage. Unit of measure: Index. Geographic coverage: ASS 2011 State Suburb Code (SSC). Catalogue number: 2033.0.55.001
